  <annotatorImplementationName>fr.univnantes.lina.uima.models.Wrapper</annotatorImplementationName>
  <analysisEngineMetaData>
    <name>Term Extractor Wrapper</name>
    <description>This Analysis Engine wraps external tools as follows: 

Initialy, it runs a program called 'do-initialize' assuming it has one file parameter for the collection:
  do-initialize &lt;collection&gt;

Then, for each CAS, it applies a program called 'do-process' which is supposed to have 3 file parameters, the first for the input document, the second for the output document and the last for the collection:
  do-process &lt;input document&gt;  &lt;output document&gt; &lt;collection&gt;

Finally, it lanches a last program called 'do-finalize' wh=ich file parameter stands for the collection: 
  do-finalize &lt;collection&gt;

These programs can be set by the single-valued String parameters respectively called 'InitializeProgramFile', 'ProcessProgramFile' and 'FinalizeProgramFile'.

The collection file can be defined by the sinlge-valued String parameter 'OutputResultFile'.

Sofas to process can also be defined by the means of the multi-valued String parameter called 'SofaNames'.

This Analysis Engine uses a resource in order to (1) produced document input files for the 'do-process' program and (2) scans the document output file of this program. More precisely, it produces Tab-Separated-Values files where each line is formatted as follows from TreeTaggerAnnotation features: 

&lt;coveredText&gt;	&lt;tag&gt;	&lt;lemma&gt;	&lt;begin&gt;	&lt;end&gt;

It scans TSV files and indexes annotations of type TermAnnotation which features are formatted as follows: 

&lt;partOfSpeech&gt;	&lt;coveredText&gt;	&lt;lemma&gt;	&lt;begin&gt;	&lt;end&gt;	&lt;id&gt;
</description>
    <version>11-06-06</version>
    <vendor>University of Nantes (LINA, UMR CNRS 6241)</vendor>
